5:["$","article",null,{"className":"mx-auto flex max-w-2xl flex-col px-6 py-16","children":[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"[{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"Article\",\"headline\":\"apps · services · libs: the only three folders we let ourselves have\",\"url\":\"http://blog.stack.localhost:1355/apps-services-libs\",\"mainEntityOfPage\":\"http://blog.stack.localhost:1355/apps-services-libs\",\"description\":\"Why builders-stack splits code by who consumes it — not by feature or by tech — and how that one rule stopped us from restructuring the repo every quarter.\",\"datePublished\":\"2026-06-24\",\"dateModified\":\"2026-07-02\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Person\",\"name\":\"The builders-stack team\"}},{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BreadcrumbList\",\"itemListElement\":[{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":1,\"name\":\"Blog\",\"item\":\"http://blog.stack.localhost:1355/\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":2,\"name\":\"apps · services · libs: the only three folders we let ourselves have\",\"item\":\"http://blog.stack.localhost:1355/apps-services-libs\"}]}]"}}],["$","$L10",null,{"href":"/","className":"mb-8 text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground","children":"← All posts"}],["$","header",null,{"className":"mb-8 flex flex-col gap-4","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground","children":[["$","time",null,{"dateTime":"2026-06-24","children":"June 24, 2026"}],["$","span",null,{"aria-hidden":true,"children":"·"}],["$","span",null,{"children":"The builders-stack team"}],[["$","span",null,{"aria-hidden":true,"children":"·"}],["$","span",null,{"children":["Updated ","July 2, 2026"]}]]]}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight","children":"apps · services · libs: the only three folders we let ourselves have"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg text-muted-foreground","children":"Why builders-stack splits code by who consumes it — not by feature or by tech — and how that one rule stopped us from restructuring the repo every quarter."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex flex-wrap gap-2","children":[["$","span","structure",{"data-slot":"badge","className":"inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-1 rounded-md border px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium w-fit whitespace-nowrap shrink-0 transition-colors overflow-hidden [&>svg]:size-3 [&>svg]:pointer-events-none focus-visible:border-ring focus-visible:ring-ring/50 focus-visible:ring-[3px] aria-invalid:border-destructive aria-invalid:ring-destructive/20 border-transparent bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground","children":"structure"}],["$","span","monorepo",{"data-slot":"badge","className":"inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-1 rounded-md border px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium w-fit whitespace-nowrap shrink-0 transition-colors overflow-hidden [&>svg]:size-3 [&>svg]:pointer-events-none focus-visible:border-ring focus-visible:ring-ring/50 focus-visible:ring-[3px] aria-invalid:border-destructive aria-invalid:ring-destructive/20 border-transparent bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground","children":"monorepo"}],["$","span","nx",{"data-slot":"badge","className":"inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-1 rounded-md border px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium w-fit whitespace-nowrap shrink-0 transition-colors overflow-hidden [&>svg]:size-3 [&>svg]:pointer-events-none focus-visible:border-ring focus-visible:ring-ring/50 focus-visible:ring-[3px] aria-invalid:border-destructive aria-invalid:ring-destructive/20 border-transparent bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground","children":"nx"}]]}]]}],"$L11"]}]
11:["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"my-4 leading-7 text-foreground/90","children":["Every repo I have watched rot died the same way: not from bad code, but from nobody\nagreeing where code goes. A ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"utils/"}]," that became a landfill. A ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"components/"}]," folder\nthree teams imported from in three incompatible ways. Six months in, half of every PR\nreview was an argument about placement, and the answer changed depending on who showed\nup. builders-stack has exactly three top-level code folders, and the rule that picks\nbetween them is boring on purpose."]}],"\n",["$","h2",null,{"className":"mt-12 mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight","children":"Split by exposure, not by feature"}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"className":"my-4 leading-7 text-foreground/90","children":"The question we answer for every new piece of code is not \"what does it do\" but \"who is\nallowed to consume it\":"}],"\n",["$","ul",null,{"className":"my-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-foreground/90","children":["\n",["$","li",null,{"className":"leading-7","children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"apps/"}]}]," — something a human opens. ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"apps/web"}]," (the flagship), ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"apps/landing"}]," (the\nmarketing site), ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"apps/blog"}]," (what you're reading), ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"apps/mobile"}],". If it renders to a\nperson, it's an app."]}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"className":"leading-7","children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"services/"}]}]," — a deployable backend with a URL. ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"services/api"}]," (Hono + Better\nAuth), ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"services/payment"}],". If something calls it over the network, it's a service."]}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"className":"leading-7","children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"libs/"}]}]," — shared code imported by package name, never a deep path. ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"@stack/ui"}],",\n",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"@stack/db"}],", ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"@stack/seo"}],", ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"@stack/config"}],". If more than one app or service needs it,\nit's a lib."]}],"\n"]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"className":"my-4 leading-7 text-foreground/90","children":["That's the whole taxonomy. The payoff is that you never restructure — you only add. A\nnew surface is a new folder under ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"apps/"}],". A new integration is a new ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"@stack/*"}]," lib.\nThe shape of the repo on day 500 is the shape on day 1, just wider."]}],"\n",["$","h2",null,{"className":"mt-12 mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight","children":"The boundaries have teeth"}],"\n","$L12","\n","$L13","\n","$L14","\n","$L15","\n","$L16"]}]
12:["$","p",null,{"className":"my-4 leading-7 text-foreground/90","children":["A convention nobody enforces is a suggestion, and suggestions lose to deadlines. Nx tags\nevery project (",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"type:app"}],", ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"type:lib"}],", ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"type:service"}],") and enforces the dependency\ndirection between them, so an app can't reach into another app's internals and a lib\ncan't import an app. The rule isn't in a wiki where it gets ignored — it's in\n",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"nx.json"}]," and it fails ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"nx run-many -t lint"}],"."]}]
13:["$","p",null,{"className":"my-4 leading-7 text-foreground/90","children":["The subtle part is that Nx can only resolve ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"@stack/*"}]," to enforce those constraints\nbecause the same import paths are declared once in ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"tsconfig.base.json"}],". One ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"paths"}],"\nblock is doing double duty: TypeScript resolution and boundary enforcement. When we\nadded this very blog, wiring it up was three lines — a workspace member, an ",["$","code",null,{"className":"rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm","children":"nx.tags"}],"\nentry, and one path — precisely because the structure already had a slot shaped like it."]}]
14:["$","h2",null,{"className":"mt-12 mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight","children":"Why an agent cares"}]
15:["$","p",null,{"className":"my-4 leading-7 text-foreground/90","children":["The reason this matters more in 2026 than it did five years ago is that a coding agent\nnavigates a repo the same way a new hire does — by inferring the rules from the shape.\nA folder named by ",["$","em",null,{"children":"exposure"}]," tells the agent where a thing goes without it having to\nread every file first. We wrote more about how we make the public surfaces legible to\ncrawlers and agents in ",["$","a",null,{"className":"font-medium text-primary underline underline-offset-4","href":"/seo-as-a-build-gate","children":"SEO you can't forget to do"}],"."]}]
16:["$","p",null,{"className":"my-4 leading-7 text-foreground/90","children":"The lesson wasn't \"use a monorepo\". It was that the folder taxonomy is a decision you\nmake once, cheaply, at the start — and pay for forever if you skip it."}]
